# SQL files are byte-compared by Go gates (TestBaselineFileIsFrozen pins the
# sha256 of internal/store/migrations/00001_baseline.sql; the drift canary
# byte-compares internal/store/schema_snapshot.sql against a regeneration).
# Force LF normalization on checkout so a contributor on Windows with
# core.autocrlf=true cannot trip those gates with a phantom CRLF rewrite they
# never authored.
#
# [LAW:one-source-of-truth] The bytes on disk must equal the bytes the embed
# package sees, on every platform, every checkout. A platform-dependent
# normalization is a second source the gates cannot distinguish from a real
# edit.
*.sql text eol=lf
